SASentry.name: entry1
SASentry.Title: test data for desmearing

SASprocess.name: creation
SASprocess.SASprocessnote: These data were computed to have Guinier behavior at low Q and Porod at high Q with a flat background noise. The "smeared" SASdata is used to test desmearing software. Typical input parameters are shown.

SASprocess.name: canSAS1d/1.0 XML formatter
SASprocess.SASprocessnote: formatting of text data into canSAS XML 1D standard

SASentry.SASnote: The SAS is not expected to be interpreted into a physical model.
The C-language version of lake was used to prepare the desmeared output with the typical parameters above.

The Python version of lake (derived from lake-c) was used to prepare the desmeared output with the typical parameters above. This version was built with separate modules for smear, desmear, extrapolation, etc. and should be easier to support and upgrade for the long-term.

The Python version of lake (directly translated from lake.for) was used to prepare the desmeared output with the typical parameters above. This version was built to closely match the original FORTRAN program (which does not compile now).
The IgorPro version of lake (in the Irena tool suite) was used to prepare the desmeared output with the typical parameters above.
